name: Issue 6 [Print]
description: Issue #6 launched on 6 September 2013. This issue features queer performance icon Glitta Supernova, cabaret sensation Le Gateau Chocolat, San Francisco-based photographer Robbie Sweeny, electro pop duo Double Duchess, the naked Russian Pavel Petel interviewed by Bobby Petty, Sydney photographer Tina Fiveash interviewed by Urszula Dawkins, the bent and spectacular Glitter Militia, queer pornographer Courtney Trouble interviewed by Louise Malcolm, and centrefold feature by creative powerhouse Annabelle Gaspar. The issue also includes "Quick and Dirty" features with Izzy and Fernando. Cover image and more information Published in September 2013. Prices are in Australian Dollars. All deliveries in plain packaging.

name: Issue 5 [Print]
description: Issue #5 features Original Plumbing’s Amos Mac, genderqueer pornographer Jiz Lee interviewed by burlesque star Lillian Starr, Melbourne musicians Mojo Juju and Clairy Browne in a vintage inspired shoot with Frankie Valentine, co-founder of “Against Equality” Ryan Conrad, Kate Bornstein on “radical welcoming” in queer communities, Canadian bear photographer Inked Kenny interviewed by Bobby Petty, Sydney Mr Leather 2012/The Naked Barber Richard Savvy, as well as Colin Kinchela, Guy Whitworth, Joy, Razz and Sam Wallman. Slideshow and more information Published in September 2012. Prices are in Australian Dollars. All deliveries in plain packaging.

name: Issue 4 [Print]
description: Issue #4 features the greatest cabaret artist of a generation Mx Justin Vivian Bond, godfather of burlesque Tigger!, our Queers in Wonderland centrefold, singer and minimalist musician Peaches, Fancy Piece talking queer performance, DJs Gemma and Seymour Butz of Club Kooky; and 'Quick and Dirty' features on Kam and George, Kelly and Spencer, Jo, and Aaron. Slideshow and more information Published in February 2012. Prices are in Australian Dollars. All deliveries in plain packaging.

name: Issue 3 [Print]
description: Issue 3 features William Yang, human unicorn Danni Daniels, Emilie Jouvet (the French movie producer behind Too Much Pussy!), our Sydney Bears centrefold, an interview with artist Ana Wojak, Melbourne photographer and club promoter Nik Dimopoulos, and Jez Pez from DUDE Trans Male Zine. It also includes "Quick and Dirty" features on TJ, Matty, and Megan and Sarah. Slideshow and more information Published in September 2011. Prices are in Australian Dollars. All deliveries in plain packaging.

name: Issue 2 [Print]
description: Issue 2 includes: Bruce LaBruce talking about LA Zombie and François Sagat, Australian artist Arlene TextaQueen, Barcelona's Luis Pedro de Castro, our Trans man footy team centrefold, JD Samson interviewed, plus Christopher Schulz from PINUPS talking about bears and an interview with Ireland's top pig-dog-man-woman Miss Panti. IT also includes "Quick and Dirty" features on Thy Anh, Grant, and Matt Parsons. Slideshow and more information Published in February 2011. Prices are in Australian Dollars. All deliveries in plain packaging.

name: Issue 1 [Print]
description: LIMITED STOCK REMAINING Our first issue includes photoshoots and interview with Sydney Femme Guild, “Revolutionary bodies” by photographer and herm activist Del LaGrace Volcano, LA artist-model-actor Trevor Wayne, our “Hard Yakka” centrefold, plus Melbourne bad boy photostudio Bad Behaviour, “Money shots” by Torrie Torrie, and ten years of Sydney’s Bad Dog parties. It also includes “Quick and Dirty” features on Gavin, Benn and Craig, Chris, Josef and Jez. Slideshow and more information Published in September 2010. Prices are in Australian Dollars. All deliveries in plain packaging.
